 obtained using a range of shell-model interactions. The YSOX\nshell-model Hamiltonian, the cross-shell part of which is based on the\nmonopole-based universal interaction, was found to provide a very good\ndescription of the present results and those for the neighbouring odd-A carbon\nisotopes - in particular for the negative parity cross-shell states.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Dec 2022 03:13:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-04"}
